cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on developing a model for recognizing Vietnamese handwritten text, which involves image processing and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the model also uses an attention-based LSTM network for generating output text, it could also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves training the model end-to-end, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, since the paper evaluates the model's performance on datasets, it could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
